The paper discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for facial surface and texture synthesis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of 3D morphable models (3DMM), which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and involves optimization (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a novel methodology for face synthesis, which involves learning and generating new data, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
